20:04.400 --> 20:05.040
Stochastic.

20:05.600 --> 20:08.000
Meaning it uses random noise.

20:08.180 --> 20:08.440
Yes.

20:08.960 --> 20:12.380
Thermal jitter, random molecular or computational motion.

20:12.520 --> 20:12.700
Yeah.

20:12.900 --> 20:17.080
The system uses this noise to slowly drift along the tangential manifold.

20:17.320 --> 20:17.680
Okay.

20:17.680 --> 20:22.660
It explores all the other possible configurations that are also truthful configurations.

20:23.160 --> 20:28.720
Where you're still holding the glass, but it specifically seeks out regions of low curvature.

20:28.980 --> 20:30.640
It's looking for a flat area.

20:30.780 --> 20:31.300
Exactly.

20:31.860 --> 20:35.900
So after I catch the glass, I slowly shift my stance.

20:36.160 --> 20:37.660
I untwist my back.

20:37.660 --> 20:40.700
I bring my arm closer to my center of gravity.

20:41.100 --> 20:44.100
I distribute my weight evenly across my feet.

20:44.680 --> 20:49.800
I am still perfectly honoring the truth of the event the glass is safe, but I've drifted

20:49.800 --> 20:54.800
into a physical posture that I can maintain for hours without cramping.

20:54.960 --> 21:02.320
And that transition from the awkward catch to the sustainable posture is how Flyxion and

21:02.320 --> 21:07.720
draws the mathematical distinction between being correct and being wise.

21:07.980 --> 21:08.760
Oh, wow.

21:08.860 --> 21:10.020
I love that terminology.

21:10.300 --> 21:12.040
Wisdom is a geometric property.

21:12.620 --> 21:14.840
It is a beautiful formalization, isn't it?

21:15.160 --> 21:18.380
The normal snap makes a system truthful.

21:18.760 --> 21:20.760
It aligns with the raw data.

