The normal snap is the elastic response.

34:31.320 --> 34:36.300
It's a stiff, instantaneous reaction to stress, snapping to logical truth.

34:36.300 --> 34:39.960
The tangential drift is the viscous response.

34:40.920 --> 34:46.580
It's the slow, dampening slide through the honey to find the flat, low-curvature valley.

34:46.720 --> 34:48.200
Catch the glass elastically.

34:48.820 --> 34:50.180
Shift your stance viscously.

34:50.500 --> 34:50.840
Yes.

34:51.420 --> 34:58.720
Now, in a healthy geometry, when a new event introduces stress, the system distributes and

34:58.720 --> 35:02.080
dissipates that stress perfectly using those two mechanisms.

35:02.240 --> 35:02.480
Right.

35:02.480 --> 35:09.440
But when the system hits a topological tear, an Escher staircase, the material of the space

35:09.440 --> 35:10.560
itself is broken.

35:11.120 --> 35:13.120
The space can't bend, so it breaks.

35:13.340 --> 35:13.640
Yes.

35:14.300 --> 35:16.020
The stress cannot be distributed.

35:16.740 --> 35:21.920
The elastic normal snap violently deposits the system right next to the defect because that

35:21.920 --> 35:23.520
is where the local truth lies.

35:23.700 --> 35:24.060
Okay.

35:24.060 --> 35:29.640
But the viscous tangential drift cannot carry the system away to a flat, safe area because

35:29.640 --> 35:32.960
there is no continuous geometric path to a safe area.

35:33.620 --> 35:34.880
The manifold is torn.

35:35.400 --> 35:40.880
So you are trapped in a state of high-curvature, high-tension, and you physically can't drift

35:40.880 --> 35:41.240
away.

35:41.600 --> 35:45.620
And this creates a very specific, observable behavioral loop.

35:45.620 --> 35:51.460
Flyxion outlines a triple-diagnostic signature that mathematically proves the system is stuck

35:51.460 --> 35:54.900
in an obstruction rather than just processing normal data.

35:54.900 --> 35:55.400
Okay.

35:55.580 --> 35:56.720
We need to know the signatures.

